{% block content %}
    <h1>Gutter Cleaning in Port Coquitlam — Prevent Water Damage Before It Starts</h1>

    <p>Port Coquitlam’s proximity to the Coquitlam River, dense greenbelts, and mature residential areas creates ideal conditions for clogged gutters. Falling leaves, small branches, roof grit, and moss collect quickly inside drainage channels, especially during fall and winter storms. When water cannot move freely, it begins to overflow — placing unnecessary stress on roofing edges, siding, and foundations.</p>

    <p>Clean Gutters Crew (CGC) provides professional gutter cleaning services across Port Coquitlam to help homeowners stay ahead of costly repairs. Our team understands how local weather patterns and tree coverage impact homes in this part of the Tri-Cities.</p>

    <p>We work throughout Central Port Coquitlam, Citadel Heights, Mary Hill, Riverwood, Oxford Heights, Glenwood, Lincoln Park, and surrounding neighbourhoods. Homes backing onto parks or forested areas typically require more frequent maintenance, and we are fully equipped to handle those high-debris environments safely and efficiently.</p>

    <h2>Why Port Coquitlam Homes Need Routine Maintenance</h2>

    <p>When gutters remain blocked, rainwater can spill over rooflines and accumulate around the base of the structure. Over time, this may contribute to soil erosion, basement dampness, weakened fascia boards, and premature material deterioration. Excess moisture also increases the risk of mold development in hidden areas.</p>

    <p>Consistent cleaning ensures proper drainage performance and helps preserve the overall condition of your property.</p>

    <h2>Our Professional Cleaning Process</h2>

    <p>CGC removes organic buildup using specialized tools designed for residential systems. Downspouts are cleared, water flow is tested, and the entire channel network is checked for signs of misalignment or wear. We focus on prevention — identifying small concerns before they turn into expensive repairs.</p>

    <p>Our crew works carefully around roofing materials and landscaping, leaving your property clean and orderly when the service is complete.</p>

    <h2>Why Homeowners Choose CGC in Port Coquitlam</h2>

    <ul>
        <li>Quick scheduling and reliable arrival times</li>
        <li>Experience with river-adjacent and greenbelt properties</li>
        <li>Clear, upfront pricing</li>
        <li>Detail-focused workmanship</li>
        <li>Preventative approach to home protection</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Regular gutter maintenance is one of the simplest ways to protect your Port Coquitlam home from unnecessary water damage.</p>

    <p><strong>Book your free estimate today and keep your drainage system performing at its best.</strong></p>
